types.name: OrderLineItem
types.description:
Represents a line item in an order.Each line item describes a different
product to purchase, with its own quantity and price details.
Permissions: ORDERS_READ

fields.name: appliedDiscounts
fields.description:
The list of references to discounts applied to this line item. Each
`OrderLineItemAppliedDiscount` has a `discount_uid` that references the `uid` of a top-level
`OrderLineItemDiscounts` applied to the line item. On reads, the amount
applied is populated.
  
An `OrderLineItemAppliedDiscount` is automatically created on every line item for all
`ORDER` scoped discounts that are added to the order. `OrderLineItemAppliedDiscount` records
for `LINE_ITEM` scoped discounts must be added in requests for the discount to apply to any
line items.
  
To change the amount of a discount, modify the referenced top-level discount.

fields.name: appliedServiceCharges
fields.description:
The list of references to service charges applied to this line item. Each
`OrderLineItemAppliedServiceCharge` has a `service_charge_id` that references the `uid` of a
top-level `OrderServiceCharge` applied to the line item. On reads, the amount applied is
populated.
  
To change the amount of a service charge, modify the referenced top-level service charge.

fields.name: appliedTaxes
fields.description:
The list of references to taxes applied to this line item. Each
`OrderLineItemAppliedTax` has a `tax_uid` that references the `uid` of a
top-level `OrderLineItemTax` applied to the line item. On reads, the
amount applied is populated.
  
An `OrderLineItemAppliedTax` is automatically created on every line
item for all `ORDER` scoped taxes added to the order. `OrderLineItemAppliedTax`
records for `LINE_ITEM` scoped taxes must be added in requests for the tax
to apply to any line items.
  
To change the amount of a tax, modify the referenced top-level tax.

fields.name: basePrice
fields.description: The base price for a single unit of the line item.

fields.name: basePriceMoney
fields.description: The base price for a single unit of the line item.

fields.name: grossSales
fields.description: The amount of money made in gross sales for this line item.

fields.name: grossSalesMoney
fields.description:
The amount of money made in gross sales for this line item.
The amount is calculated as the sum of the variation's total price and each modifier's total price.
For inclusive tax items in the US, Canada, and Japan, tax is deducted from `gross_sales_money`. For Europe and
Australia, inclusive tax remains as part of the gross sale calculation.

fields.name: itemType
fields.description:
The type of line item: an itemized sale, a non-itemized sale (custom amount), or the
activation or reloading of a gift card.

fields.name: itemVariation
fields.description: The CatalogItemVariation ID applied to this line item.

fields.name: metadata
fields.description:
Application-defined data attached to this line item. Metadata fields are intended
to store descriptive references or associations with an entity in another system or store brief
information about the object. Square does not process this field; it only stores and returns it
in relevant API calls. Do not use metadata to store any sensitive information (such as personally
identifiable information or card details).
  
Keys written by applications must be 60 characters or less and must be in the character set
`[a-zA-Z0-9_-]`. Entries can also include metadata generated by Square. These keys are prefixed
with a namespace, separated from the key with a ':' character.
  
Values have a maximum length of 255 characters.
  
An application can have up to 10 entries per metadata field.
  
Entries written by applications are private and can only be read or modified by the same
application.
  
For more information, see [Metadata](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/build-basics/metadata).

fields.name: modifiers
fields.description: The CatalogModifiers applied to this line item.

fields.name: name
fields.description: The name of the line item.

fields.name: note
fields.description: An optional note associated with the line item.

fields.name: pricingBlocklists
fields.description:
Describes pricing adjustments that are blocked from automatic
application to a line item. For more information, see
[Apply Taxes and Discounts](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/orders-api/apply-taxes-and-discounts).

fields.name: quantity
fields.description:
The count, or measurement, of a line item being purchased:
  
If `quantity` is a whole number, and `quantity_unit` is not specified, then `quantity` denotes an item count.  For example: `3` apples.
  
If `quantity` is a whole or decimal number, and `quantity_unit` is also specified, then `quantity` denotes a measurement.  For example: `2.25` pounds of broccoli.
  
For more information, see [Specify item quantity and measurement unit](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/orders-api/create-orders#specify-item-quantity-and-measurement-unit).
  
Line items with a quantity of `0` are automatically removed
when paying for or otherwise completing the order.

fields.name: quantityUnit
fields.description: The measurement unit and decimal precision that this line item's quantity is measured in.

fields.name: totalDiscount
fields.description: The total amount of discount money to collect for the line item.

fields.name: totalDiscountMoney
fields.description: The total amount of discount money to collect for the line item.

fields.name: totalMoney
fields.description: The total amount of money to collect for this line item.

fields.name: totalServiceCharge
fields.description: The total amount of apportioned service charge money to collect for the line item.

fields.name: totalServiceChargeMoney
fields.description: The total amount of apportioned service charge money to collect for the line item.

fields.name: totalTax
fields.description: The total amount of tax money to collect for the line item.

fields.name: totalTaxMoney
fields.description: The total amount of tax money to collect for the line item.

fields.name: uid
fields.description: A unique ID that identifies the line item only within this order.

fields.name: variationTotalPrice
fields.description: The total price of all item variations sold in this line item.

fields.name: variationTotalPriceMoney
fields.description:
The total price of all item variations sold in this line item.
The price is calculated as `base_price_money` multiplied by `quantity`.
It does not include modifiers.

types.name: OrderLineItemAppliedDiscount
types.description:
Represents an applied portion of a discount to a line item in an order.Order scoped discounts have automatically applied discounts present for each line item.
Line-item scoped discounts must have applied discounts added manually for any applicable line
items. The corresponding applied money is automatically computed based on participating
line items.
Permissions: ORDERS_READ

fields.name: appliedMoney
fields.description: The amount of money applied by the discount to the line item.

fields.name: discountUid
fields.description:
The `uid` of the discount that the applied discount represents. It must
reference a discount present in the `order.discounts` field.
  
This field is immutable. To change which discounts apply to a line item,
you must delete the discount and re-add it as a new `OrderLineItemAppliedDiscount`.

fields.name: uid
fields.description: A unique ID that identifies the applied discount only within this order.

types.name: OrderLineItemAppliedServiceCharge
types.description: Permissions: ORDERS_READ

fields.name: appliedMoney
fields.description: The amount of money applied by the service charge to the line item.

fields.name: serviceChargeUid
fields.description:
The `uid` of the service charge that the applied service charge represents. It must
reference a service charge present in the `order.service_charges` field.
  
This field is immutable. To change which service charges apply to a line item,
delete and add a new `OrderLineItemAppliedServiceCharge`.

fields.name: uid
fields.description: A unique ID that identifies the applied service charge only within this order.

types.name: OrderLineItemAppliedTax
types.description:
Represents an applied portion of a tax to a line item in an order.Order-scoped taxes automatically include the applied taxes in each line item.
Line item taxes must be referenced from any applicable line items.
The corresponding applied money is automatically computed, based on the
set of participating line items.
Permissions: ORDERS_READ

fields.name: appliedMoney
fields.description: The amount of money applied by the tax to the line item.

fields.name: taxUid
fields.description:
The `uid` of the tax for which this applied tax represents. It must reference
a tax present in the `order.taxes` field.
  
This field is immutable. To change which taxes apply to a line item, delete and add a new
`OrderLineItemAppliedTax`.

fields.name: uid
fields.description: A unique ID that identifies the applied tax only within this order.

types.name: OrderLineItemDiscount
types.description:
Represents a discount that applies to one or more line items in an
order.Fixed-amount, order-scoped discounts are distributed across all non-zero line item totals.
The amount distributed to each line item is relative to the
amount contributed by the item to the order subtotal.
Permissions: ORDERS_READ

fields.name: amount
fields.description: The total declared monetary amount of the discount.

fields.name: amountMoney
fields.description:
The total declared monetary amount of the discount.
  
`amount_money` is not set for percentage-based discounts.

fields.name: appliedMoney
fields.description:
The amount of discount actually applied to the line item.
  
The amount represents the amount of money applied as a line-item scoped discount.
When an amount-based discount is scoped to the entire order, the value
of `applied_money` is different than `amount_money` because the total
amount of the discount is distributed across all line items.

fields.name: discount
fields.description: The catalog object ID referencing CatalogDiscount.

fields.name: discountCodeIds
fields.description: The discount code IDs corresponding to this discount.

fields.name: metadata
fields.description:
Application-defined data attached to this discount. Metadata fields are intended
to store descriptive references or associations with an entity in another system or store brief
information about the object. Square does not process this field; it only stores and returns it
in relevant API calls. Do not use metadata to store any sensitive information (such as personally
identifiable information or card details).
  
Keys written by applications must be 60 characters or less and must be in the character set
`[a-zA-Z0-9_-]`. Entries can also include metadata generated by Square. These keys are prefixed
with a namespace, separated from the key with a ':' character.
  
Values have a maximum length of 255 characters.
  
An application can have up to 10 entries per metadata field.
  
Entries written by applications are private and can only be read or modified by the same
application.
  
For more information, see [Metadata](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/build-basics/metadata).

fields.name: name
fields.description: The discount's name.

fields.name: percentage
fields.description:
The percentage of the discount, as a string representation of a decimal number.
A value of `7.25` corresponds to a percentage of 7.25%.
  
`percentage` is not set for amount-based discounts.

fields.name: pricingRule
fields.description:
The object ID of a pricing rule to be applied
automatically to this discount. The specification and application of the discounts, to
which a `pricing_rule_id` is assigned, are completely controlled by the corresponding
pricing rule.

fields.name: rewards
fields.description:
The reward IDs corresponding to this discount. The application and
specification of discounts that have `reward_ids` are completely controlled by the backing
criteria corresponding to the reward tiers of the rewards that are added to the order
through the Loyalty API. To manually unapply discounts that are the result of added rewards,
the rewards must be removed from the order through the Loyalty API.

fields.name: scope
fields.description:
Indicates the level at which the discount applies. For `ORDER` scoped discounts,
Square generates references in `applied_discounts` on all order line items that do
not have them. For `LINE_ITEM` scoped discounts, the discount only applies to line items
with a discount reference in their `applied_discounts` field.
  
This field is immutable. To change the scope of a discount, you must delete
the discount and re-add it as a new discount.

fields.name: type
fields.description:
The type of the discount.
  
Discounts that do not reference a catalog object ID must have a type of
`FIXED_PERCENTAGE` or `FIXED_AMOUNT`.

fields.name: uid
fields.description: A unique ID that identifies the discount only within this order.

types.name: OrderLineItemDiscountScope
types.description: Indicates whether this is a line-item or order-level discount.

enumValues.name: LINE_ITEM
enumValues.description:
The discount should be applied to only line items specified by
`OrderLineItemAppliedDiscount` reference records.

enumValues.name: ORDER
enumValues.description: The discount should be applied to the entire order.

enumValues.name: OTHER_DISCOUNT_SCOPE
enumValues.description:
Used for reporting only.
The original transaction discount scope is currently not supported by the API.

types.name: OrderLineItemDiscountType
types.description: Indicates how the discount is applied to the associated line item or order.

enumValues.name: FIXED_AMOUNT
enumValues.description: Apply the discount as a fixed monetary value (such as $1.00) off the item price.

enumValues.name: FIXED_PERCENTAGE
enumValues.description: Apply the discount as a fixed percentage (such as 5%) off the item price.

enumValues.name: UNKNOWN_DISCOUNT
enumValues.description:
Used for reporting only.
The original transaction discount type is currently not supported by the API.

enumValues.name: VARIABLE_AMOUNT
enumValues.description:
Apply the discount as a variable amount based on the item price.
  
The specific discount amount of a `VARIABLE_AMOUNT` discount
is assigned at the time of the purchase.

enumValues.name: VARIABLE_PERCENTAGE
enumValues.description:
Apply the discount as a variable percentage based on the item
price.
  
The specific discount percentage of a `VARIABLE_PERCENTAGE` discount
is assigned at the time of the purchase.

types.name: OrderLineItemItemType
types.description: Represents the line item type.

enumValues.name: CUSTOM_AMOUNT
enumValues.description: Indicates that the line item is a non-itemized sale.

enumValues.name: GIFT_CARD
enumValues.description:
Indicates that the line item is a gift card sale. Gift cards sold through
the Orders API are sold in an unactivated state and can be activated through the
Gift Cards API using the line item `uid`.

enumValues.name: ITEM
enumValues.description: Indicates that the line item is an itemized sale.

types.name: OrderLineItemModifier
types.description:
A CatalogModifier.
Permissions: ORDERS_READ

fields.name: basePrice
fields.description: The base price for the modifier.

fields.name: metadata
fields.description:
Application-defined data attached to this order. Metadata fields are intended
to store descriptive references or associations with an entity in another system or store brief
information about the object. Square does not process this field; it only stores and returns it
in relevant API calls. Do not use metadata to store any sensitive information (such as personally
identifiable information or card details).
  
Keys written by applications must be 60 characters or less and must be in the character set
`[a-zA-Z0-9_-]`. Entries can also include metadata generated by Square. These keys are prefixed
with a namespace, separated from the key with a ':' character.
  
Values have a maximum length of 255 characters.
  
An application can have up to 10 entries per metadata field.
  
Entries written by applications are private and can only be read or modified by the same
application.
  
For more information, see  [Metadata](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/build-basics/metadata).

fields.name: modifier
fields.description: The catalog object ID referencing CatalogModifier.

fields.name: name
fields.description: The name of the item modifier.

fields.name: quantity
fields.description:
The quantity of the line item modifier. The modifier quantity can be 0 or more.
For example, suppose a restaurant offers a cheeseburger on the menu. When a buyer orders
this item, the restaurant records the purchase by creating an `Order` object with a line item
for a burger. The line item includes a line item modifier: the name is cheese and the quantity
is 1. The buyer has the option to order extra cheese (or no cheese). If the buyer chooses
the extra cheese option, the modifier quantity increases to 2. If the buyer does not want
any cheese, the modifier quantity is set to 0.

fields.name: totalPrice
fields.description: The total price of the item modifier for its line item.

fields.name: uid
fields.description: A unique ID that identifies the modifier only within this order.

types.name: OrderLineItemPricingBlocklists
types.description:
Describes pricing adjustments that are blocked from automatic
application to a line item.For more information, see
[Apply Taxes and Discounts](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/orders-api/apply-taxes-and-discounts).
Permissions: ORDERS_READ

fields.name: blockedDiscounts
fields.description:
A list of discounts blocked from applying to the line item.
Discounts can be blocked by the `discount_uid` (for ad hoc discounts) or
the `discount_catalog_object_id` (for catalog discounts).

fields.name: blockedTaxes
fields.description:
A list of taxes blocked from applying to the line item.
Taxes can be blocked by the `tax_uid` (for ad hoc taxes) or
the `tax_catalog_object_id` (for catalog taxes).

types.name: OrderLineItemPricingBlocklistsBlockedDiscount
types.description:
A discount to block from applying to a line item.The discount must be
identified by either `discount_uid` or `discount_catalog_object_id`, but not both.
Permissions: ORDERS_READ

fields.name: discountCatalogObjectId
fields.description:
The `catalog_object_id` of the discount that should be blocked.
Use this field to block catalog discounts. For ad hoc discounts, use the
`discount_uid` field.

fields.name: discountUid
fields.description:
The `uid` of the discount that should be blocked. Use this field to block
ad hoc discounts. For catalog discounts, use the `discount_catalog_object_id` field.

fields.name: uid
fields.description: A unique ID of the `BlockedDiscount` within the order.

types.name: OrderLineItemPricingBlocklistsBlockedTax
types.description:
A tax to block from applying to a line item.The tax must be
identified by either `tax_uid` or `tax_catalog_object_id`, but not both.
Permissions: ORDERS_READ

fields.name: taxCatalogObjectId
fields.description:
The `catalog_object_id` of the tax that should be blocked.
Use this field to block catalog taxes. For ad hoc taxes, use the
`tax_uid` field.

fields.name: taxUid
fields.description:
The `uid` of the tax that should be blocked. Use this field to block
ad hoc taxes. For catalog, taxes use the `tax_catalog_object_id` field.

fields.name: uid
fields.description: A unique ID of the `BlockedTax` within the order.

types.name: OrderLineItemTax
types.description:
Represents a tax that applies to one or more line item in the order.Fixed-amount, order-scoped taxes are distributed across all non-zero line item totals.
The amount distributed to each line item is relative to the amount the item
contributes to the order subtotal.
Permissions: ORDERS_READ

fields.name: appliedMoney
fields.description:
The amount of money applied to the order by the tax.
  
- For percentage-based taxes, `applied_money` is the money
calculated using the percentage.

fields.name: autoApplied
fields.description:
Determines whether the tax was automatically applied to the order based on
the catalog configuration. For an example, see
[Automatically Apply Taxes to an Order](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/orders-api/apply-taxes-and-discounts/auto-apply-taxes).

fields.name: metadata
fields.description:
Application-defined data attached to this tax. Metadata fields are intended
to store descriptive references or associations with an entity in another system or store brief
information about the object. Square does not process this field; it only stores and returns it
in relevant API calls. Do not use metadata to store any sensitive information (such as personally
identifiable information or card details).
  
Keys written by applications must be 60 characters or less and must be in the character set
`[a-zA-Z0-9_-]`. Entries can also include metadata generated by Square. These keys are prefixed
with a namespace, separated from the key with a ':' character.
  
Values have a maximum length of 255 characters.
  
An application can have up to 10 entries per metadata field.
  
Entries written by applications are private and can only be read or modified by the same
application.
  
For more information, see [Metadata](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/build-basics/metadata).

fields.name: name
fields.description: The tax's name.

fields.name: percentage
fields.description:
The percentage of the tax, as a string representation of a decimal
number. For example, a value of `"7.25"` corresponds to a percentage of
7.25%.

fields.name: scope
fields.description:
Indicates the level at which the tax applies. For `ORDER` scoped taxes,
Square generates references in `applied_taxes` on all order line items that do
not have them. For `LINE_ITEM` scoped taxes, the tax only applies to line items
with references in their `applied_taxes` field.
  
This field is immutable. To change the scope, you must delete the tax and
re-add it as a new tax.

fields.name: tax
fields.description: The catalog object ID referencing CatalogTax.

fields.name: type
fields.description: Indicates the calculation method used to apply the tax.

fields.name: uid
fields.description: A unique ID that identifies the tax only within this order.

types.name: OrderLineItemTaxScope
types.description: Indicates whether this is a line-item or order-level tax.

enumValues.name: LINE_ITEM
enumValues.description:
The tax should be applied only to line items specified by
the `OrderLineItemAppliedTax` reference records.

enumValues.name: ORDER
enumValues.description: The tax should be applied to the entire order.

enumValues.name: OTHER_TAX_SCOPE
enumValues.description:
Used for reporting only.
The original transaction tax scope is currently not supported by the API.

types.name: OrderLineItemTaxType
types.description: Indicates how the tax is applied to the associated line item or order.

enumValues.name: ADDITIVE
enumValues.description:
The tax is an additive tax. The tax amount is added on top of the price.
For example, an item with a cost of 1.00 USD and a 10% additive tax has a total
cost to the buyer of 1.10 USD.

enumValues.name: INCLUSIVE
enumValues.description:
The tax is an inclusive tax. Inclusive taxes are already included
in the line item price or order total. For example, an item with a cost of
1.00 USD and a 10% inclusive tax has a pretax cost of 0.91 USD
(91 cents) and a 0.09 (9 cents) tax for a total cost of 1.00 USD to
the buyer.

enumValues.name: UNKNOWN_TAX
enumValues.description:
Used for reporting only.
The original transaction tax type is currently not supported by the API.

types.name: OrderMoneyAmounts
types.description:
A collection of various money amounts.
Permissions: ORDERS_READ

fields.name: discount
fields.description: The money associated with discounts.

fields.name: serviceCharge
fields.description: The money associated with service charges.

fields.name: tax
fields.description: The money associated with taxes.

fields.name: tip
fields.description: The money associated with tips.

fields.name: totalMoney
fields.description: The total money.

types.name: OrderOtherTender
types.description: Permissions: ORDERS_READ

fields.name: amount
fields.description: The total amount of the tender, including `tip_money`. If the tender has a `payment_id`, the `total_money` of the corresponding Payment will be equal to the `amount_money` of the tender.

fields.name: amountMoney
fields.description:
The total amount of the tender, including `tip_money`. If the tender has a `payment_id`,
the `total_money` of the corresponding Payment will be equal to the
`amount_money` of the tender.

fields.name: createdAt
fields.description:
The timestamp for when the tender was created, in RFC 3339 format.
  
Examples for January 25th, 2020 6:25:34pm Pacific Standard Time:
  
UTC:  2020-01-26T02:25:34Z
  
Pacific Standard Time with UTC offset:  2020-01-25T18:25:34-08:00

fields.name: customer
fields.description:
If the tender is associated with a customer or represents a customer's card on file,
this is the ID of the associated customer.

fields.name: id
fields.description: The tender's unique ID. It is the associated payment ID.

fields.name: location
fields.description: The ID of the transaction's associated location.

fields.name: merchantId
fields.description: The Square-issued ID of the merchant.

fields.name: note
fields.description: An optional note associated with the tender at the time of payment.

fields.name: payment
fields.description:
The ID of the Payment that corresponds to this tender.
This value is only present for payments created with the v2 Payments API.

fields.name: processingFee
fields.description: The amount of any Square processing fees applied to the tender.

fields.name: processingFeeMoney
fields.description:
The amount of any Square processing fees applied to the tender.
  
This field is not immediately populated when a new transaction is created.
It is usually available after about ten seconds.

fields.name: tip
fields.description: The tip's amount of the tender.

fields.name: tipMoney
fields.description: The tip's amount of the tender.

fields.name: transactionId
fields.description: The ID of the tender's associated transaction.

fields.name: type
fields.description: The type of tender, such as `CARD` or `CASH`.

types.name: OrderPickup
types.description:
Contains details necessary to fulfill a pickup order.
Permissions: ORDERS_READ

fields.name: acceptedAt
fields.description:
The [timestamp](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/build-basics/working-with-dates)
indicating when the fulfillment was marked in progress. The timestamp must be in RFC 3339 format
(for example, "2016-09-04T23:59:33.123Z").
  
Examples for January 25th, 2020 6:25:34pm Pacific Standard Time:
  
UTC:  2020-01-26T02:25:34Z
  
Pacific Standard Time with UTC offset:  2020-01-25T18:25:34-08:00

fields.name: autoCompleteDuration
fields.description:
The duration of time after which an in progress pickup fulfillment is automatically moved
to the `COMPLETED` state. The duration must be in RFC 3339 format (for example, "P1W3D").
  
If not set, this pickup fulfillment remains in progress until it is canceled or completed.
  
Example for 2 days, 12 hours, 30 minutes, and 15 seconds: P2DT12H30M15S

fields.name: cancelReason
fields.description: A description of why the pickup was canceled. The maximum length: 100 characters.

fields.name: canceledAt
fields.description:
The [timestamp](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/build-basics/working-with-dates)
indicating when the fulfillment was canceled. The timestamp must be in RFC 3339 format
(for example, "2016-09-04T23:59:33.123Z").
  
Examples for January 25th, 2020 6:25:34pm Pacific Standard Time:
  
UTC:  2020-01-26T02:25:34Z
  
Pacific Standard Time with UTC offset:  2020-01-25T18:25:34-08:00

fields.name: curbsidePickup
fields.description: Specific details for curbside pickup. These details can only be populated if `is_curbside_pickup` is set to `true`.

fields.name: expiredAt
fields.description:
The [timestamp](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/build-basics/working-with-dates)
indicating when the fulfillment expired. The timestamp must be in RFC 3339 format
(for example, "2016-09-04T23:59:33.123Z").
  
Examples for January 25th, 2020 6:25:34pm Pacific Standard Time:
  
UTC:  2020-01-26T02:25:34Z
  
Pacific Standard Time with UTC offset:  2020-01-25T18:25:34-08:00

fields.name: expiresAt
fields.description:
The [timestamp](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/build-basics/working-with-dates)
indicating when this fulfillment expires if it is not marked in progress. The timestamp must be
in RFC 3339 format (for example, "2016-09-04T23:59:33.123Z"). The expiration time can only be set
up to 7 days in the future. If `expires_at` is not set, any new payments attached to the order
are automatically completed.
  
Examples for January 25th, 2020 6:25:34pm Pacific Standard Time:
  
UTC:  2020-01-26T02:25:34Z
  
Pacific Standard Time with UTC offset:  2020-01-25T18:25:34-08:00

fields.name: isCurbsidePickup
fields.description: If set to `true`, indicates that this pickup order is for curbside pickup, not in-store pickup.

fields.name: note
fields.description:
A note to provide additional instructions about the pickup
fulfillment displayed in the Square Point of Sale application and set by the API.

fields.name: pickedUpAt
fields.description:
The [timestamp](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/build-basics/working-with-dates)
indicating when the fulfillment was picked up by the recipient. The timestamp must be in RFC 3339 format
(for example, "2016-09-04T23:59:33.123Z").
  
Examples for January 25th, 2020 6:25:34pm Pacific Standard Time:
  
UTC:  2020-01-26T02:25:34Z
  
Pacific Standard Time with UTC offset:  2020-01-25T18:25:34-08:00

fields.name: pickupAt
fields.description:
The [timestamp](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/build-basics/working-with-dates)
that represents the start of the pickup window. Must be in RFC 3339 timestamp format, e.g.,
"2016-09-04T23:59:33.123Z".
  
For fulfillments with the schedule type `ASAP`, this is automatically set
to the current time plus the expected duration to prepare the fulfillment.
  
Examples for January 25th, 2020 6:25:34pm Pacific Standard Time:
  
UTC:  2020-01-26T02:25:34Z
  
Pacific Standard Time with UTC offset:  2020-01-25T18:25:34-08:00

fields.name: pickupWindowDuration
fields.description:
The window of time in which the order should be picked up after the `pickup_at` timestamp.
Must be in RFC 3339 duration format, e.g., "P1W3D". Can be used as an
informational guideline for merchants.
  
Example for 2 days, 12 hours, 30 minutes, and 15 seconds: P2DT12H30M15S

fields.name: placedAt
fields.description:
The [timestamp](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/build-basics/working-with-dates)
indicating when the fulfillment was placed. The timestamp must be in RFC 3339 format
(for example, "2016-09-04T23:59:33.123Z").
  
Examples for January 25th, 2020 6:25:34pm Pacific Standard Time:
  
UTC:  2020-01-26T02:25:34Z
  
Pacific Standard Time with UTC offset:  2020-01-25T18:25:34-08:00

fields.name: prepTimeDuration
fields.description:
The duration of time it takes to prepare this fulfillment.
The duration must be in RFC 3339 format (for example, "P1W3D").
  
Example for 2 days, 12 hours, 30 minutes, and 15 seconds: P2DT12H30M15S

fields.name: readyAt
fields.description:
The [timestamp](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/build-basics/working-with-dates)
indicating when the fulfillment is marked as ready for pickup. The timestamp must be in RFC 3339 format
(for example, "2016-09-04T23:59:33.123Z").
  
Examples for January 25th, 2020 6:25:34pm Pacific Standard Time:
  
UTC:  2020-01-26T02:25:34Z
  
Pacific Standard Time with UTC offset:  2020-01-25T18:25:34-08:00

fields.name: recipient
fields.description:
Information about the person to pick up this fulfillment from a physical
location.

fields.name: rejectedAt
fields.description:
The [timestamp](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/build-basics/working-with-dates)
indicating when the fulfillment was rejected. The timestamp must be in RFC 3339 format
(for example, "2016-09-04T23:59:33.123Z").
  
Examples for January 25th, 2020 6:25:34pm Pacific Standard Time:
  
UTC:  2020-01-26T02:25:34Z
  
Pacific Standard Time with UTC offset:  2020-01-25T18:25:34-08:00

fields.name: scheduleType
fields.description: The schedule type of the pickup fulfillment. Defaults to `SCHEDULED`.

types.name: OrderPickupScheduleType
types.description: The schedule type of the pickup fulfillment.

enumValues.name: ASAP
enumValues.description:
Indicates that the fulfillment will be picked up as soon as possible and
should be prepared immediately.

enumValues.name: SCHEDULED
enumValues.description: Indicates that the fulfillment will be picked up at a scheduled pickup time.

types.name: OrderPricingOptions
types.description:
Pricing options for an order.The options affect how the order's price is calculated.
They can be used, for example, to apply automatic price adjustments that are based on preconfigured
pricing rules.
Permissions: ORDERS_READ

fields.name: autoApplyDiscounts
fields.description:
The option to determine whether pricing rule-based
discounts are automatically applied to an order.

fields.name: autoApplyTaxes
fields.description:
The option to determine whether rule-based taxes are automatically
applied to an order when the criteria of the corresponding rules are met.

types.name: OrderQuantityUnit
types.description:
Contains the measurement unit for a quantity and a precision that
specifies the number of digits after the decimal point for decimal quantities.
Permissions: ORDERS_READ

fields.name: catalogObjectId
fields.description:
The catalog object ID referencing the
CatalogMeasurementUnit.
  
This field is set when this is a catalog-backed measurement unit.

fields.name: measurementUnit
fields.description:
A MeasurementUnit that represents the
unit of measure for the quantity.

fields.name: precision
fields.description:
For non-integer quantities, represents the number of digits after the decimal point that are
recorded for this quantity.
  
For example, a precision of 1 allows quantities such as `"1.0"` and `"1.1"`, but not `"1.01"`.
  
Min: 0. Max: 5.

types.name: OrderReturn
types.description:
The set of line items, service charges, taxes, discounts, tips, and other items being returned in an order.
Permissions: ORDERS_READ

fields.name: amounts
fields.description: An aggregate monetary value being returned by this return entry.

fields.name: discounts
fields.description:
A collection of references to discounts being returned for an order, including the total
applied discount amount to be returned. The discounts must reference a top-level discount ID
from the source order.

fields.name: lineItems
fields.description: A collection of line items that are being returned.

fields.name: returnTips
fields.description: A collection of references to tips being returned for an order.

fields.name: roundingAdjustment
fields.description:
A positive or negative rounding adjustment to the total value being returned. Adjustments are commonly
used to apply cash rounding when the minimum unit of the account is smaller than the lowest
physical denomination of the currency.

fields.name: serviceCharges
fields.description: A collection of service charges that are being returned.

fields.name: source
fields.description:
An order that contains the original sale of these return line items. This is unset
for unlinked returns.

fields.name: taxes
fields.description:
A collection of references to taxes being returned for an order, including the total
applied tax amount to be returned. The taxes must reference a top-level tax ID from the source
order.

fields.name: uid
fields.description: A unique ID that identifies the return only within this order.

types.name: OrderReturnDiscount
types.description:
Represents a discount being returned that applies to one or more return line items in an
order.Fixed-amount, order-scoped discounts are distributed across all non-zero return line item totals.
The amount distributed to each return line item is relative to that items contribution to the
order subtotal.
Permissions: ORDERS_READ

fields.name: amount
fields.description: The total declared monetary amount of the discount.

fields.name: amountMoney
fields.description:
The total declared monetary amount of the discount.
  
`amount_money` is not set for percentage-based discounts.

fields.name: appliedMoney
fields.description:
The amount of discount actually applied to this line item. When an amount-based
discount is at the order level, this value is different from `amount_money` because the discount
is distributed across the line items.

fields.name: discount
fields.description: The catalog object ID referencing CatalogDiscount.

fields.name: name
fields.description: The discount's name.

fields.name: percentage
fields.description:
The percentage of the tax, as a string representation of a decimal number.
A value of `"7.25"` corresponds to a percentage of 7.25%.
  
`percentage` is not set for amount-based discounts.

fields.name: scope
fields.description:
Indicates the level at which the `OrderReturnDiscount` applies. For `ORDER` scoped
discounts, the server generates references in `applied_discounts` on all
`OrderReturnLineItem`s. For `LINE_ITEM` scoped discounts, the discount is only applied to
`OrderReturnLineItem`s with references in their `applied_discounts` field.

fields.name: sourceDiscountUid
fields.description: The discount `uid` from the order that contains the original application of this discount.

fields.name: type
fields.description:
The type of the discount. If it is created by the API, it is `FIXED_PERCENTAGE` or `FIXED_AMOUNT`.
  
Discounts that do not reference a catalog object ID must have a type of
`FIXED_PERCENTAGE` or `FIXED_AMOUNT`.

fields.name: uid
fields.description: A unique ID that identifies the returned discount only within this order.

types.name: OrderReturnLineItem
types.description:
The line item being returned in an order.
Permissions: ORDERS_READ

fields.name: appliedDiscounts
fields.description:
The list of references to `OrderReturnDiscount` entities applied to the return line item. Each
`OrderLineItemAppliedDiscount` has a `discount_uid` that references the `uid` of a top-level
`OrderReturnDiscount` applied to the return line item. On reads, the applied amount
is populated.

fields.name: appliedServiceCharges
fields.description:
The list of references to `OrderReturnServiceCharge` entities applied to the return
line item. Each `OrderLineItemAppliedServiceCharge` has a `service_charge_uid` that
references the `uid` of a top-level `OrderReturnServiceCharge` applied to the return line
item. On reads, the applied amount is populated.

fields.name: appliedTaxes
fields.description:
The list of references to `OrderReturnTax` entities applied to the return line item. Each
`OrderLineItemAppliedTax` has a `tax_uid` that references the `uid` of a top-level
`OrderReturnTax` applied to the return line item. On reads, the applied amount
is populated.

fields.name: basePrice
fields.description: The base price for a single unit of the line item.

fields.name: basePriceMoney
fields.description: The base price for a single unit of the line item.

fields.name: grossReturn
fields.description: The gross return amount of money calculated as (item base price + modifiers price) * quantity.

fields.name: grossReturnMoney
fields.description: The gross return amount of money calculated as (item base price + modifiers price) * quantity.

fields.name: itemVariation
fields.description: The CatalogItemVariation ID applied to this return line item.

fields.name: modifiers
fields.description: The CatalogModifiers applied to this line item.

fields.name: name
fields.description: The name of the line item.

fields.name: note
fields.description: The note of the return line item.

fields.name: quantity
fields.description:
The quantity returned, formatted as a decimal number.
For example, `"3"`.
  
Line items with a `quantity_unit` can have non-integer quantities.
For example, `"1.70000"`.

fields.name: quantityUnit
fields.description: The unit and precision that this return line item's quantity is measured in.

fields.name: sourceLineItemUid
fields.description: The `uid` of the line item in the original sale order.

fields.name: totalDiscount
fields.description: The total amount of discount money to return for the line item.

fields.name: totalDiscountMoney
fields.description: The total amount of discount money to return for the line item.

fields.name: totalMoney
fields.description: The total amount of money to return for this line item.

fields.name: totalServiceCharge
fields.description: The total amount of apportioned service charge money to return for the line item.

fields.name: totalServiceChargeMoney
fields.description: The total amount of apportioned service charge money to return for the line item.

fields.name: totalTax
fields.description: The total amount of tax money to return for the line item.

fields.name: totalTaxMoney
fields.description: The total amount of tax money to return for the line item.

fields.name: uid
fields.description: A unique ID for this return line-item entry.

fields.name: variationName
fields.description: The name of the variation applied to this return line item.

fields.name: variationTotalPrice
fields.description: The total price of all item variations returned in this line item.

fields.name: variationTotalPriceMoney
fields.description:
The total price of all item variations returned in this line item.
The price is calculated as `base_price_money` multiplied by `quantity` and
does not include modifiers.

types.name: OrderReturnLineItemModifier
types.description:
A line item modifier being returned.
Permissions: ORDERS_READ

fields.name: basePrice
fields.description: The base price for the modifier.

fields.name: modifier
fields.description: The catalog object ID referencing CatalogModifier.

fields.name: name
fields.description: The name of the item modifier.

fields.name: quantity
fields.description:
The quantity of the line item modifier. The modifier quantity can be 0 or more.
For example, suppose a restaurant offers a cheeseburger on the menu. When a buyer orders
this item, the restaurant records the purchase by creating an `Order` object with a line item
for a burger. The line item includes a line item modifier: the name is cheese and the quantity
is 1. The buyer has the option to order extra cheese (or no cheese). If the buyer chooses
the extra cheese option, the modifier quantity increases to 2. If the buyer does not want
any cheese, the modifier quantity is set to 0.

fields.name: sourceModifierUid
fields.description:
The modifier `uid` from the order's line item that contains the
original sale of this line item modifier.

fields.name: totalPrice
fields.description: The total price of the item modifier for its line item.

fields.name: uid
fields.description: A unique ID that identifies the return modifier only within this order.

types.name: OrderReturnServiceCharge
types.description:
Represents the service charge applied to the original order.
Permissions: ORDERS_READ

fields.name: amount
fields.description: The amount of a non-percentage-based service charge.

fields.name: amountMoney
fields.description:
The amount of a non-percentage-based service charge.
  
Either `percentage` or `amount_money` should be set, but not both.

fields.name: appliedMoney
fields.description:
The amount of money applied to the order by the service charge, including
any inclusive tax amounts, as calculated by Square.
  
- For fixed-amount service charges, `applied_money` is equal to `amount_money`.
- For percentage-based service charges, `applied_money` is the money calculated using the percentage.

fields.name: appliedTaxes
fields.description:
The list of references to `OrderReturnTax` entities applied to the
`OrderReturnServiceCharge`. Each `OrderLineItemAppliedTax` has a `tax_uid`
that references the `uid` of a top-level `OrderReturnTax` that is being
applied to the `OrderReturnServiceCharge`. On reads, the applied amount is
populated.

fields.name: calculationPhase
fields.description: The calculation phase after which to apply the service charge.

fields.name: name
fields.description: The name of the service charge.

fields.name: percentage
fields.description:
The percentage of the service charge, as a string representation of
a decimal number. For example, a value of `"7.25"` corresponds to a
percentage of 7.25%.
  
Either `percentage` or `amount_money` should be set, but not both.

fields.name: scope
fields.description:
Indicates the level at which the apportioned service charge applies. For `ORDER`
scoped service charges, Square generates references in `applied_service_charges` on
all order line items that do not have them. For `LINE_ITEM` scoped service charges,
the service charge only applies to line items with a service charge reference in their
`applied_service_charges` field.
  
This field is immutable. To change the scope of an apportioned service charge, you must delete
the apportioned service charge and re-add it as a new apportioned service charge.

fields.name: serviceCharge
fields.description: The catalog object ID of the associated OrderServiceCharge.

fields.name: sourceServiceChargeUid
fields.description:
The service charge `uid` from the order containing the original
service charge. `source_service_charge_uid` is `null` for
unlinked returns.

fields.name: taxable
fields.description:
Indicates whether the surcharge can be taxed. Service charges
calculated in the `TOTAL_PHASE` cannot be marked as taxable.

fields.name: totalMoney
fields.description:
The total amount of money to collect for the service charge.
  
__NOTE__: If an inclusive tax is applied to the service charge, `total_money`
does not equal `applied_money` plus `total_tax_money` because the inclusive
tax amount is already included in both `applied_money` and `total_tax_money`.

fields.name: totalTax
fields.description: The total amount of tax money to collect for the service charge.

fields.name: totalTaxMoney
fields.description: The total amount of tax money to collect for the service charge.

fields.name: treatmentType
fields.description: The treatment type of the service charge.

fields.name: uid
fields.description: A unique ID that identifies the return service charge only within this order.

types.name: OrderReturnTax
types.description:
Represents a tax being returned that applies to one or more return line items in an order.Fixed-amount, order-scoped taxes are distributed across all non-zero return line item totals.
The amount distributed to each return line item is relative to that items contribution to the
order subtotal.
Permissions: ORDERS_READ

fields.name: appliedMoney
fields.description: The amount of money applied by the tax in an order.

fields.name: name
fields.description: The tax's name.

fields.name: percentage
fields.description:
The percentage of the tax, as a string representation of a decimal number.
For example, a value of `"7.25"` corresponds to a percentage of 7.25%.

fields.name: scope
fields.description:
Indicates the level at which the `OrderReturnTax` applies. For `ORDER` scoped
taxes, Square generates references in `applied_taxes` on all
`OrderReturnLineItem`s. For `LINE_ITEM` scoped taxes, the tax is only applied to
`OrderReturnLineItem`s with references in their `applied_discounts` field.

fields.name: sourceTaxUid
fields.description: The tax `uid` from the order that contains the original tax charge.

fields.name: tax
fields.description: The catalog object ID referencing CatalogTax.

fields.name: type
fields.description: Indicates the calculation method used to apply the tax.

fields.name: uid
fields.description: A unique ID that identifies the returned tax only within this order.

types.name: OrderReturnTip
types.description:
A tip being returned.
Permissions: ORDERS_READ

fields.name: appliedMoney
fields.description:
The amount of tip being returned
--

fields.name: sourceTenderId
fields.description: The tender `id` from the order that contains the original application of this tip.

fields.name: sourceTenderUid
fields.description: The tender `uid` from the order that contains the original application of this tip.

fields.name: uid
fields.description: A unique ID that identifies the tip only within this order.

types.name: OrderRoundingAdjustment
types.description:
A rounding adjustment of the money being returned.Commonly used to apply cash rounding
when the minimum unit of the account is smaller than the lowest physical denomination of the currency.
Permissions: ORDERS_READ

fields.name: amount
fields.description: The actual rounding adjustment amount.

fields.name: amountMoney
fields.description: The actual rounding adjustment amount.

fields.name: name
fields.description: The name of the rounding adjustment from the original sale order.

fields.name: uid
fields.description: A unique ID that identifies the rounding adjustment only within this order.

types.name: OrderServiceCharge
types.description:
Represents a service charge applied to an order.
Permissions: ORDERS_READ

fields.name: amount
fields.description: The amount of a non-percentage-based service charge.

fields.name: amountMoney
fields.description:
The amount of a non-percentage-based service charge.
  
Exactly one of `percentage` or `amount_money` should be set.

fields.name: appliedMoney
fields.description:
The amount of money applied to the order by the service charge,
including any inclusive tax amounts, as calculated by Square.
  
- For fixed-amount service charges, `applied_money` is equal to `amount_money`.
- For percentage-based service charges, `applied_money` is the money
calculated using the percentage.

fields.name: appliedTaxes
fields.description:
The list of references to the taxes applied to this service charge. Each
`OrderLineItemAppliedTax` has a `tax_uid` that references the `uid` of a top-level
`OrderLineItemTax` that is being applied to this service charge. On reads, the amount applied
is populated.
  
An `OrderLineItemAppliedTax` is automatically created on every taxable service charge
for all `ORDER` scoped taxes that are added to the order. `OrderLineItemAppliedTax` records
for `LINE_ITEM` scoped taxes must be added in requests for the tax to apply to any taxable
service charge. Taxable service charges have the `taxable` field set to `true` and calculated
in the `SUBTOTAL_PHASE`.
  
To change the amount of a tax, modify the referenced top-level tax.

fields.name: calculationPhase
fields.description: The calculation phase at which to apply the service charge.

fields.name: metadata
fields.description:
Application-defined data attached to this service charge. Metadata fields are intended
to store descriptive references or associations with an entity in another system or store brief
information about the object. Square does not process this field; it only stores and returns it
in relevant API calls. Do not use metadata to store any sensitive information (such as personally
identifiable information or card details).
  
Keys written by applications must be 60 characters or less and must be in the character set
`[a-zA-Z0-9_-]`. Entries can also include metadata generated by Square. These keys are prefixed
with a namespace, separated from the key with a ':' character.
  
Values have a maximum length of 255 characters.
  
An application can have up to 10 entries per metadata field.
  
Entries written by applications are private and can only be read or modified by the same
application.
  
For more information, see [Metadata](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/build-basics/metadata).

fields.name: name
fields.description: The name of the service charge.

fields.name: percentage
fields.description:
The service charge percentage as a string representation of a
decimal number. For example, `"7.25"` indicates a service charge of 7.25%.
  
Exactly 1 of `percentage` or `amount_money` should be set.

fields.name: scope
fields.description:
Indicates the level at which the apportioned service charge applies. For `ORDER`
scoped service charges, Square generates references in `applied_service_charges` on
all order line items that do not have them. For `LINE_ITEM` scoped service charges,
the service charge only applies to line items with a service charge reference in their
`applied_service_charges` field.
  
This field is immutable. To change the scope of an apportioned service charge, you must delete
the apportioned service charge and re-add it as a new apportioned service charge.

fields.name: serviceCharge
fields.description: The catalog object ID referencing the service charge CatalogObject.

fields.name: taxable
fields.description:
Indicates whether the service charge can be taxed. If set to `true`,
order-level taxes automatically apply to the service charge. Note that
service charges calculated in the `TOTAL_PHASE` cannot be marked as taxable.

fields.name: totalMoney
fields.description:
The total amount of money to collect for the service charge.
  
__Note__: If an inclusive tax is applied to the service charge,
`total_money` does not equal `applied_money` plus `total_tax_money`
because the inclusive tax amount is already included in both
`applied_money` and `total_tax_money`.

fields.name: totalTax
fields.description: The total amount of money to collect for the service charge.

fields.name: totalTaxMoney
fields.description: The total amount of tax money to collect for the service charge.

fields.name: treatmentType
fields.description: The treatment type of the service charge.

fields.name: type
fields.description: The type of the service charge.

fields.name: uid
fields.description: A unique ID that identifies the service charge only within this order.

types.name: OrderServiceChargeCalculationPhase
types.description:
Represents a phase in the process of calculating order totals.Service charges are applied after the indicated phase.

[Read more about how order totals are calculated.](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/orders-api/how-it-works#how-totals-are-calculated)

enumValues.name: APPORTIONED_AMOUNT_PHASE
enumValues.description:
The service charge is calculated as a compounding adjustment
after any discounts and percentage based apportioned service charges,
but before any tax considerations.

enumValues.name: APPORTIONED_PERCENTAGE_PHASE
enumValues.description:
The service charge is calculated as a compounding adjustment
after any discounts, but before amount based apportioned service charges
and any tax considerations.

enumValues.name: SUBTOTAL_PHASE
enumValues.description:
The service charge is applied after discounts, but before
taxes.

enumValues.name: TOTAL_PHASE
enumValues.description:
The service charge is applied after all discounts and taxes
are applied.

types.name: OrderServiceChargeScope
types.description:
Indicates whether this is a line-item or order-level apportioned
service charge.

enumValues.name: LINE_ITEM
enumValues.description:
The service charge should be applied to only line items specified by
`OrderLineItemAppliedServiceCharge` reference records.

enumValues.name: ORDER
enumValues.description: The service charge should be applied to the entire order.

enumValues.name: OTHER_SERVICE_CHARGE_SCOPE
enumValues.description:
Used for reporting only.
The original transaction service charge scope is currently not supported by the API.

types.name: OrderServiceChargeTreatmentType
types.description:
Indicates whether the service charge will be treated as a value-holding line item or
apportioned toward a line item.

types.name: OrderServiceChargeType
types.description: Orders service charge type enum.

enumValues.name: AUTO_GRATUITY
enumValues.description: The service charge is an automatic gratuity.

enumValues.name: CUSTOM
enumValues.description: The service charge is a custom amount.

types.name: OrderShipment
types.description:
Contains the details necessary to fulfill a shipment order.
Permissions: ORDERS_READ

fields.name: cancelReason
fields.description: A description of why the shipment was canceled.

fields.name: canceledAt
fields.description:
The [timestamp](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/build-basics/working-with-dates)
indicating the shipment was canceled.
The timestamp must be in RFC 3339 format (for example, "2016-09-04T23:59:33.123Z").
  
Examples for January 25th, 2020 6:25:34pm Pacific Standard Time:
  
UTC:  2020-01-26T02:25:34Z
  
Pacific Standard Time with UTC offset:  2020-01-25T18:25:34-08:00

fields.name: carrier
fields.description: The shipping carrier being used to ship this fulfillment (such as UPS, FedEx, or USPS).

fields.name: expectedShippedAt
fields.description:
The [timestamp](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/build-basics/working-with-dates)
indicating when the shipment is expected to be delivered to the shipping carrier.
The timestamp must be in RFC 3339 format (for example, "2016-09-04T23:59:33.123Z").
  
Examples for January 25th, 2020 6:25:34pm Pacific Standard Time:
  
UTC:  2020-01-26T02:25:34Z
  
Pacific Standard Time with UTC offset:  2020-01-25T18:25:34-08:00

fields.name: failedAt
fields.description:
The [timestamp](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/build-basics/working-with-dates)
indicating when the shipment failed to be completed. The timestamp must be in RFC 3339 format
(for example, "2016-09-04T23:59:33.123Z").
  
Examples for January 25th, 2020 6:25:34pm Pacific Standard Time:
  
UTC:  2020-01-26T02:25:34Z
  
Pacific Standard Time with UTC offset:  2020-01-25T18:25:34-08:00

fields.name: failureReason
fields.description: A description of why the shipment failed to be completed.

fields.name: inProgressAt
fields.description:
The [timestamp](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/build-basics/working-with-dates)
indicating when this fulfillment was moved to the `RESERVED` state, which  indicates that preparation
of this shipment has begun. The timestamp must be in RFC 3339 format (for example, "2016-09-04T23:59:33.123Z").
  
Examples for January 25th, 2020 6:25:34pm Pacific Standard Time:
  
UTC:  2020-01-26T02:25:34Z
  
Pacific Standard Time with UTC offset:  2020-01-25T18:25:34-08:00

fields.name: packagedAt
fields.description:
The [timestamp](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/build-basics/working-with-dates)
indicating when this fulfillment was moved to the `PREPARED` state, which indicates that the
fulfillment is packaged. The timestamp must be in RFC 3339 format (for example, "2016-09-04T23:59:33.123Z").
  
Examples for January 25th, 2020 6:25:34pm Pacific Standard Time:
  
UTC:  2020-01-26T02:25:34Z
  
Pacific Standard Time with UTC offset:  2020-01-25T18:25:34-08:00

fields.name: placedAt
fields.description:
The [timestamp](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/build-basics/working-with-dates)
indicating when the shipment was requested. The timestamp must be in RFC 3339 format
(for example, "2016-09-04T23:59:33.123Z").
  
Examples for January 25th, 2020 6:25:34pm Pacific Standard Time:
  
UTC:  2020-01-26T02:25:34Z
  
Pacific Standard Time with UTC offset:  2020-01-25T18:25:34-08:00

fields.name: recipient
fields.description: Information about the person to receive this shipment fulfillment.

fields.name: shippedAt
fields.description:
The [timestamp](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/build-basics/working-with-dates)
indicating when this fulfillment was moved to the `COMPLETED` state, which indicates that
the fulfillment has been given to the shipping carrier. The timestamp must be in RFC 3339 format
(for example, "2016-09-04T23:59:33.123Z").
  
Examples for January 25th, 2020 6:25:34pm Pacific Standard Time:
  
UTC:  2020-01-26T02:25:34Z
  
Pacific Standard Time with UTC offset:  2020-01-25T18:25:34-08:00

fields.name: shippingNote
fields.description: A note with additional information for the shipping carrier.

fields.name: shippingType
fields.description:
A description of the type of shipping product purchased from the carrier
(such as First Class, Priority, or Express).

fields.name: trackingNumber
fields.description: The reference number provided by the carrier to track the shipment's progress.

fields.name: trackingUrl
fields.description: A link to the tracking webpage on the carrier's website.

types.name: OrderSort
types.description:
Criteria to sort results by. The chronological order in which results are returned. Defaults to createdAt_DESC.

When using a BasicDateTimeFilter, OrderSort must match the timestamp field that the BasicDateTimeFilter uses to filter. For example, If you set your sort_field to closedAt and you use a BasicDateTimeFilter,
your BasicDateTimeFilter must filter for orders by their closedAt date. If this field does not match the timestamp field in BasicDateTimeFilter, it will return an error.

types.name: OrderSource
types.description:
Represents the origination details of an order.
Permissions: ORDERS_READ

fields.name: name
fields.description:
The name used to identify the place (physical or digital) that an order originates.
If unset, the name defaults to the name of the application that created the order.

types.name: OrderSquareAccountTender
types.description:
Represents the details of a tender with `type` `SQUARE_ACCOUNT`.
Permissions: ORDERS_READ

fields.name: amount
fields.description: The total amount of the tender, including `tip_money`. If the tender has a `payment_id`, the `total_money` of the corresponding Payment will be equal to the `amount_money` of the tender.

fields.name: amountMoney

The total amount of the tender, including `tip_money`. If the tender has a `payment_id`,
the `total_money` of the corresponding Payment will be equal to the
`amount_money` of the tender.

UTC:  2020-01-26T02:25:34Z
  
Pacific Standard Time with UTC offset:  2020-01-25T18:25:34-08:00

fields.name: customer

If the tender is associated with a customer or represents a customer's card on file,

fields.name: processingFeeMoney

The amount of any Square processing fees applied to the tender.
  
This field is not immediately populated when a new transaction is created.
It is usually available after about ten seconds.

fields.name: status
fields.description:
The Square Account payment's current state (such as `AUTHORIZED` or

fields.name: tip

fields.description: The tip's amount of the tender.

fields.name: type

types.name: OrderSquareAccountTenderStatus
types.description: Orders tender square account detail status enum.

enumValues.name: AUTHORIZED
enumValues.description: The Square Account payment has been authorized but not yet captured.

enumValues.name: CAPTURED
enumValues.description: The Square Account payment was authorized and subsequently captured (i.e., completed).

enumValues.name: VOIDED
enumValues.description: The Square Account payment was authorized and subsequently voided (i.e., canceled).

types.name: OrderState
types.description: The state of the order.

enumValues.name: CANCELED
enumValues.description: Indicates that the order is canceled. Canceled orders are not paid. This is a terminal state.

enumValues.name: COMPLETED
enumValues.description: Indicates that the order is completed. Completed orders are fully paid. This is a terminal state.

enumValues.name: DRAFT
enumValues.description:
Indicates that the order is in a draft state. Draft orders can be updated,
but cannot be paid or fulfilled.
For more information, see [Create Orders](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/orders-api/create-orders).

enumValues.name: OPEN
enumValues.description: Indicates that the order is open. Open orders can be updated.

types.name: OrderStateFilter
types.description: OrderStateFilter is used for filtering a query with OrderState

inputFields.name: equalToAnyOf
inputFields.description: Used for filtering a query with OrderState

types.name: OrderTender
types.description: Represents a tender (i.e., a method of payment) used in a Square transaction. Permissions:ORDERS_READ

fields.name: amount
fields.description: The total amount of the tender, including `tip_money`. If the tender has a `payment_id`, the `total_money` of the corresponding Payment will be equal to the `amount_money` of the tender.

fields.name: amountMoney
fields.description:
The total amount of the tender, including `tip_money`. If the tender has a `payment_id`,
the `total_money` of the corresponding Payment will be equal to the
`amount_money` of the tender.

fields.name: createdAt
fields.description:
The timestamp for when the tender was created, in RFC 3339 format.
  
Examples for January 25th, 2020 6:25:34pm Pacific Standard Time:
  
UTC:  2020-01-26T02:25:34Z
  
Pacific Standard Time with UTC offset:  2020-01-25T18:25:34-08:00

fields.name: customer
fields.description:
If the tender is associated with a customer or represents a customer's card on file,
this is the ID of the associated customer.

fields.name: id
fields.description: The tender's unique ID. It is the associated payment ID.

fields.name: location
fields.description: The ID of the transaction's associated location.

fields.name: merchantId
fields.description: The Square-issued ID of the merchant.

fields.name: note
fields.description: An optional note associated with the tender at the time of payment.

fields.name: payment
fields.description:
The ID of the Payment that corresponds to this tender.
This value is only present for payments created with the v2 Payments API.

fields.name: processingFee
fields.description: The amount of any Square processing fees applied to the tender.

fields.name: processingFeeMoney
fields.description:
The amount of any Square processing fees applied to the tender.
  
This field is not immediately populated when a new transaction is created.
It is usually available after about ten seconds.

fields.name: tip
fields.description: The tip's amount of the tender.

fields.name: tipMoney
fields.description: The tip's amount of the tender.

fields.name: transactionId
fields.description: The ID of the tender's associated transaction.

fields.name: type
fields.description: The type of tender, such as `CARD` or `CASH`.

types.name: OrderTenderType
types.description: Indicates a tender's type.

enumValues.name: BUY_NOW_PAY_LATER
enumValues.description: A Buy Now Pay Later payment.

enumValues.name: NO_SALE
enumValues.description: This tender represents the register being opened for a "no sale" event.

enumValues.name: OTHER
enumValues.description: A form of tender that does not match any other value.

enumValues.name: THIRD_PARTY_CARD
enumValues.description:
A credit card processed with a card processor other than Square.
  
This value applies only to merchants in countries where Square does not
yet provide card processing.

enumValues.name: WALLET
enumValues.description:
A payment from a digital wallet, e.g. Cash App, Paypay, Rakuten Pay,
Au Pay, D Barai, Merpay, Wechat Pay, Alipay.
  
Note: Some "digital wallets", including Google Pay and Apple Pay, facilitate
card payments.  Those payments have the `CARD` type.

types.name: PageInfo
types.description: Provides pagination-related information.

fields.name: endCursor
fields.description:
The `Cursor` of the last edge of the current page. This can be passed in the next query as
a `after` argument to paginate forwards.

fields.name: hasNextPage
fields.description: Indicates if there is another page of results available after the current one.

fields.name: hasPreviousPage
fields.description: Indicates if there is another page of results available before the current one.

fields.name: startCursor
fields.description:
The `Cursor` of the first edge of the current page. This can be passed in the next query as
a `before` argument to paginate backwards.

types.name: Payment
types.description: Permissions:PAYMENTS_READ

fields.name: id
fields.description: Unique ID for the payment.

fields.name: locationId
fields.description: The ID of the location associated with the payment.

fields.name: amountMoney
fields.description:
The amount processed for this payment, not including `tipMoney`.

The amount is specified in the smallest denomination of the applicable currency (for example,
US dollar amounts are specified in cents). For more information, see
[Working with Monetary Amounts](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/build-basics/working-with-monetary-amounts).

fields.name: appFeeMoney
fields.description:
The amount the developer is taking as a fee for facilitating the payment on behalf
of the seller. This amount is specified in the smallest denomination of the applicable currency
(for example, US dollar amounts are specified in cents). For more information,
see [Take Payments and Collect Fees](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/payments-api/take-payments-and-collect-fees).

The amount cannot be more than 90% of the `total_money` value.

To set this field, `PAYMENTS_WRITE_ADDITIONAL_RECIPIENTS` OAuth permission is required.
For more information, see [Permissions](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/payments-api/take-payments-and-collect-fees#permissions).

fields.name: applicationDetails
fields.description: Details about the application that took the payment.

fields.name: approvedMoney
fields.description: The initial amount of money approved for this payment.

fields.name: bankAccountDetails
fields.description: Details about a bank account payment. These details are only populated if the `sourceType` is `BANK_ACCOUNT`.

fields.name: billingAddress
fields.description: The buyer's billing address.

fields.name: buyNowPayLaterDetails
fields.description:
Details about a Buy Now Pay Later payment. The details are only populated
if the `sourceType` is `BUY_NOW_PAY_LATER`. For more information, see
[Afterpay Payments](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/payments-api/take-payments/afterpay-payments).

fields.name: buyerEmailAddress
fields.description: The buyer's email address.

fields.name: capabilities
fields.description: Actions that can be performed on this payment.

fields.name: cardDetails
fields.description: Details about a card payment. These details are only populated if the `sourceType` is CARD.

fields.name: cashDetails
fields.description: Details about a cash payment. These details are only populated if the `sourceType` is `CASH`.

fields.name: createdAt
fields.description: The timestamp of when the payment was created, in RFC 3339 format.

fields.name: customerId
fields.description:
The [Customer](https://developer.squareup.com/reference/square/payments-api/list-payments#type-customer)
ID of the customer associated with the payment.

fields.name: delayAction
fields.description: The action to be applied to the payment when the `delayDuration` has elapsed.

fields.name: delayDuration
fields.description:
The duration of time after the payment's creation when Square automatically applies the
`delayAction` to the payment. This automatic `delayAction` applies only to payments that
don't reach a terminal state (COMPLETED, CANCELED, or FAILED) before the `delayDuration`
time period.

This field is specified as a time duration, in RFC 3339 format.

Notes:
This feature is only supported for card payments.

Default:

  - Card Present payments: "PT36H" (36 hours) from the creation time.
  - Card Not Present payments: "P7D" (7 days) from the creation time.

fields.name: delayedUntil
fields.description:
The read-only timestamp of when the `delayAction` is automatically applied,
in RFC 3339 format.

Note that this field is calculated by summing the payment's `delayDuration` and `createdAt`
fields. The `createdAt` field is generated by Square and might not exactly match the
time on your local machine.

fields.name: deviceDetails
fields.description: Details about the device that took the payment.

fields.name: externalDetails
fields.description: Details about an external payment. The details are only populated if the `sourceType` is `EXTERNAL`.

fields.name: merchantId
fields.description: The ID of the merchant associated with the payment.

fields.name: note
fields.description: An optional note to include when creating a payment.

fields.name: orderId
fields.description: The ID of the order associated with the payment.

fields.name: processingFees
fields.description: The processing fees and fee adjustments assessed by Square for this payment.

fields.name: receiptNumber
fields.description:
The payment's receipt number.
The field will be missing if a payment is canceled.

fields.name: receiptUrl
fields.description:
The URL for the payment's receipt.
The field is only populated for COMPLETED payments.

fields.name: referenceId
fields.description: An optional ID that associates this payment with an entity in another system.

fields.name: refundedMoney
fields.description:
The total amount of the payment refunded to date.

This amount is specified in the smallest denomination of the applicable currency (for example,
US dollar amounts are specified in cents).

fields.name: refunds
fields.description: The refunds for this payment.

args.name: after
args.description:
Used to forward-paginate through the `refunds`. When provided, the next page after the
provided cursor will be returned.

See the [Relay GraphQL Cursor Connections
Specification](https://relay.dev/graphql/connections.htm#sec-Arguments) for more info.

args.name: before
args.description:
Used to backward-paginate through the `refunds`. When provided, the previous page before the
provided cursor will be returned.

See the [Relay GraphQL Cursor Connections
Specification](https://relay.dev/graphql/connections.htm#sec-Arguments) for more info.

args.name: filter
args.description: Used to filter the returned `refunds` based on the provided criteria.

args.name: first
args.description:
Used in conjunction with the `after` argument to forward-paginate through the `refunds`.
When provided, limits the number of returned results to the first `n` after the provided
`after` cursor (or from the start of the `refunds`, if no `after` cursor is provided).

See the [Relay GraphQL Cursor Connections
Specification](https://relay.dev/graphql/connections.htm#sec-Arguments) for more info.

args.name: last
args.description:
Used in conjunction with the `before` argument to backward-paginate through the `refunds`.
When provided, limits the number of returned results to the last `n` before the provided
`before` cursor (or from the end of the `refunds`, if no `before` cursor is provided).

See the [Relay GraphQL Cursor Connections
Specification](https://relay.dev/graphql/connections.htm#sec-Arguments) for more info.

args.name: orderBy
args.description: Used to specify how the returned `refunds` should be sorted.

fields.name: riskEvaluation
fields.description:
Provides information about the risk associated with this payment, as determined by Square.
This field will be present for payments to sellers that have opted in to receive risk
evaluations.

fields.name: shippingAddress
fields.description: The buyer's shipping address.

fields.name: sourceType
fields.description:
The source type for the payment.

For information about these payment source types,
see [Take Payments](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/payments-api/take-payments).

fields.name: statementDescriptionIdentifier
fields.description:
Additional payment information that gets added on the customer's card statement
as part of the statement description.

Note that the `statementDescriptionIdentifier` may get truncated on the statement description
to fit the required information including the Square identifier (SQ *) and name of the
seller taking the payment.

fields.name: status
fields.description: Indicates whether the payment is APPROVED, PENDING, COMPLETED, CANCELED, or FAILED.

fields.name: teamMemberId
fields.description: An optional ID of the TeamMember associated with taking the payment.

fields.name: tipMoney
fields.description:
The amount designated as a tip.

This amount is specified in the smallest denomination of the applicable currency (for example,
US dollar amounts are specified in cents). For more information, see
[Working with Monetary Amounts](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/build-basics/working-with-monetary-amounts).

fields.name: totalMoney
fields.description:
The total amount for the payment, including `amountMoney` and `tipMoney`.

This amount is specified in the smallest denomination of the applicable currency (for example,
US dollar amounts are specified in cents). For more information, see
[Working with Monetary Amounts](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/build-basics/working-with-monetary-amounts).

fields.name: updatedAt
fields.description: The timestamp of when the payment was last updated, in RFC 3339 format.

fields.name: walletDetails
fields.description: Details about an wallet payment. The details are only populated if the `sourceType` is `WALLET`.

types.name: PaymentApplicationDetails
types.description:
Permissions: PAYMENTS_READ

Details about the application that took the payment.

fields.name: applicationId
fields.description:
The Square ID assigned to the application used to take the payment.
Application developers can use this information to identify payments that
their application processed.
For example, if a developer uses a custom application to process payments,
this field contains the application ID from the Developer Dashboard.
If a seller uses a [Square App Marketplace](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/app-marketplace)
application to process payments, the field contains the corresponding application ID.

fields.name: squareProduct
fields.description: The Square product, such as Square Point of Sale (POS), Square Invoices, or Square Virtual Terminal.

types.description: A list of products to return to external callers.

types.name: PaymentApplicationDetailsExternalSquareProductFilterInput
types.description:
Input type used to specify filters on `PaymentApplicationDetailsExternalSquareProduct` fields.

Will match all documents if passed as an empty object (or as `null`).

inputFields.name: allOf
inputFields.description:
Matches records where all of the provided sub-filters evaluate to true. This works just like an AND operator in SQL.

Note: multiple filters are automatically ANDed together. This is only needed when you have multiple filters that can't
be provided on a single
`PaymentApplicationDetailsExternalSquareProductFilterInput` input because of
collisions between key names. For example, if you want to AND multiple
OR'd sub-filters (the equivalent of (A OR B) AND (C OR D)), you could do allOf: [{anyOf: [...]}, {anyOf: [...]}].

When `null` or an empty list is passed, matches all documents.

inputFields.name: anyOf
inputFields.description:
Matches records where any of the provided sub-filters evaluate to true.
This works just like an OR operator in SQL.

When `null` is passed, matches all documents.
When an empty list is passed, this part of the filter matches no documents.

inputFields.name: equalToAnyOf
inputFields.description:
Matches records where the field value is equal to any of the provided values.
This works just like an IN operator in SQL.

When `null` is passed, matches all documents. When an empty list is passed,
this part of the filter matches no documents. When `null` is passed in the
list, this part of the filter matches records where the field value is `null`.

inputFields.name: not
inputFields.description:
Matches records where the provided sub-filter evaluates to false.
This works just like a NOT operator in SQL.

When `null` or an empty object is passed, matches no documents.

Permissions: PAYMENTS_READ
