the original payment and the amount of money refunded.


For more performant queries on this type, please filter on `merchantId` if possible.

types.description:
Permissions: PAYMENTS_READ

Represents fraud risk information for the associated payment.

When you take a payment through Square's Payments API (using the `CreatePayment`
endpoint), Square evaluates it and assigns a risk level to the payment. Sellers
can use this information to determine the course of action (for example,
provide the goods/services or refund the payment).

fields.name: createdAt
fields.description: The timestamp when payment risk was evaluated, in RFC3339 format.

fields.name: riskLevel
fields.description: The risk level associated with the payment.

types.name: PaymentRiskEvaluationFilterInput
types.description:
Input type used to specify filters on `PaymentRiskEvaluation` fields.

Will match all documents if passed as an empty object (or as `null`).

inputFields.name: createdAt
inputFields.description:
Used to filter on the `createdAt` field:

> The timestamp when payment risk was evaluated, in RFC3339 format.

When `null` or an empty object is passed, matches all documents.

inputFields.name: riskLevel
inputFields.description:
Used to filter on the `riskLevel` field:

> The risk level associated with the payment.

When `null` or an empty object is passed, matches all documents.

types.name: PaymentRiskEvaluationRiskLevel
types.description: Represents a risk level produced by evaluating a payment.

enumValues.name: HIGH
enumValues.description: Indicates significantly elevated risk level with the payment.

enumValues.name: MODERATE
enumValues.description: Indicates elevated risk level associated with the payment.

enumValues.name: NORMAL
enumValues.description: Indicates payment risk is within the normal range.

enumValues.name: PENDING
enumValues.description: Indicates Square is still evaluating the payment.

types.name: PaymentRiskEvaluationRiskLevelFilterInput
types.description:
Input type used to specify filters on `PaymentRiskEvaluationRiskLevel` fields.

Will match all documents if passed as an empty object (or as `null`).

inputFields.name: allOf
inputFields.description:
Matches records where all of the provided sub-filters evaluate to true. This works just like an AND operator in SQL.

Note: multiple filters are automatically ANDed together. This is only needed when you have multiple filters that can't
be provided on a single `PaymentRiskEvaluationRiskLevelFilterInput` input
because of collisions between key names. For example, if you want to AND multiple
OR'd sub-filters (the equivalent of (A OR B) AND (C OR D)), you could do allOf: [{anyOf: [...]}, {anyOf: [...]}].

When `null` or an empty list is passed, matches all documents.

inputFields.name: anyOf
inputFields.description:
Matches records where any of the provided sub-filters evaluate to true.
This works just like an OR operator in SQL.

When `null` is passed, matches all documents.
When an empty list is passed, this part of the filter matches no documents.

inputFields.name: equalToAnyOf
inputFields.description:
Matches records where the field value is equal to any of the provided values.
This works just like an IN operator in SQL.

When `null` is passed, matches all documents. When an empty list is passed,
this part of the filter matches no documents. When `null` is passed in the
list, this part of the filter matches records where the field value is `null`.

inputFields.name: not
inputFields.description:
Matches records where the provided sub-filter evaluates to false.
This works just like a NOT operator in SQL.

When `null` or an empty object is passed, matches no documents.

types.name: Payout
types.description:
Permissions: PAYOUTS_READ

Represents a specific payout (a money transfer) from a Square account to a seller's bank account.


For more performant queries on this type, please filter on `merchant.id` if possible.

fields.name: amountMoney
fields.description:
The amount of money involved in the payout. A positive amount indicates a
deposit, and a negative amount indicates a withdrawal. This amount is never zero.

fields.name: arrivalDate
fields.description: The calendar date, in ISO 8601 format (YYYY-MM-DD), when the payout is due to arrive in the sellers banking destination.

fields.name: createdAt
fields.description:
The timestamp of when the payout was created and submitted for deposit to the
seller's banking destination, in RFC 3339 format.

fields.name: destination
fields.description:
Information about the banking destination (such as a bank account, Square
checking account, or debit card) against which the payout was made.

fields.name: endToEndId
fields.description: A unique ID for each Payout object that might also appear on the sellers bank statement.

fields.name: id
fields.description: A unique ID for the payout.

fields.name: location
fields.description: The ID of the location associated with the payout.

fields.name: status
fields.description: Indicates the payout status.

fields.name: type
fields.description: Indicates the payout type.

fields.name: updatedAt
fields.description: The timestamp of when the payout was last updated, in RFC 3339 format.

fields.name: version
fields.description: The version number, which is incremented each time an update is made to this payout record.

types.name: PayoutConnection
types.description:
Represents a paginated collection of `Payout` results.

See the [Relay GraphQL Cursor Connections
Specification](https://relay.dev/graphql/connections.htm#sec-Connection-Types) for more info.

Permissions: PAYOUTS_READ.

fields.name: edges
fields.description: Wraps a specific `Payout` to pair it with its pagination cursor.

fields.name: pageInfo
fields.description: Provides pagination-related information.

fields.name: totalEdgeCount
fields.description: The total number of edges available in this connection to paginate over.

types.name: PayoutEdge
types.description:
Represents a specific `Payout` in the context of a `PayoutConnection`,
providing access to both the `Payout` and a pagination `Cursor`.

See the [Relay GraphQL Cursor Connections
Specification](https://relay.dev/graphql/connections.htm#sec-Edge-Types) for more info.

Permissions: PAYOUTS_READ.

fields.name: cursor
fields.description:
The `Cursor` of this `Payout`. This can be passed in the next query as
a `before` or `after` argument to continue paginating from this `Payout`.

fields.name: node
fields.description: The `Payout` of this edge.

types.name: PayoutEntry
types.description:
Permissions: PAYOUTS_READ

Payout entries for a specific payout.


For more performant queries on this type, please filter on `payoutId` if possible.

fields.name: effectiveAt
fields.description: The timestamp of when the payout entry affected the balance, in RFC 3339 format.

fields.name: feeAmountMoney
fields.description: The amount of Square fees associated with this payout entry.

fields.name: grossAmountMoney
fields.description: The amount of money involved in this payout entry.

fields.name: id
fields.description: A unique ID for the payout entry. Min Length 1.

fields.name: netAmountMoney
fields.description: The net proceeds from this transaction after any fees.

fields.name: payoutId
fields.description: The ID of the payout entries associated payout. Min Length 1.

fields.name: type
fields.description: The type of activity associated with this payout entry.

fields.name: typeAppFeeRefundDetails
fields.description: Details of a refund for an application fee on a payment.

fields.name: typeAppFeeRevenueDetails
fields.description: Revenue generated from an application fee on a payment.

fields.name: typeAutomaticSavingsDetails
fields.description: Details of any automatic transfer from the payment processing balance to the Square Savings account.

fields.name: typeAutomaticSavingsReversedDetails
fields.description: Details of any automatic transfer from the Square Savings account back to the processing balance.

fields.name: typeBalanceFoldersTransferDetails
fields.description:
Details of a transfer of funds to a banking folder. In the United States, the
folder name is 'Checking Folder'; in Canada, it's 'Balance Folder'.

fields.name: typeBalanceFoldersTransferReversedDetails
fields.description:
Details of a transfer of funds from a banking folder. In the United States,
the folder name is 'Checking Folder'; in Canada, it's 'Balance Folder'.

fields.name: typeChargeDetails
fields.description: Details of credit card payment captures.

fields.name: typeDepositFeeDetails
fields.description: Details of any fees involved with deposits such as for instant deposits.

fields.name: typeDepositFeeReversedDetails
fields.description: Details of any reversal or refund of fees involved with deposits such as for instant deposits.

fields.name: typeDisputeDetails
fields.description: Details of any balance change due to a dispute event.

fields.name: typeFeeDetails
fields.description: Details of adjustments due to the Square processing fee.

fields.name: typeFreeProcessingDetails
fields.description: Details of any credit to the merchant for the purposes of Free Processing.

fields.name: typeGiftCardLoadFeeDetails
fields.description:
Details of the fee collected during the sale or reload of a gift card. This
fee, which is a portion of the amount loaded on the gift card, is deducted
from the merchant's payment balance. The fee is recorded as a new payout
entry, not part of the CHARGE payout entry.

fields.name: typeGiftCardLoadFeeRefundDetails
fields.description: Details of a refund for the fee charged during the sale or reload of a gift card.

fields.name: typeGiftCardPoolTransferDetails
fields.description:
Details of a reversal of transfer of gift card funds from a central gift card
pool account. In franchises, when gift cards are loaded or reloaded at any
location, the money transfers to the franchisor's account.

fields.name: typeGiftCardPoolTransferReversedDetails
fields.description: Details of a refund for the fee charged during the sale or reload of a gift card.

fields.name: typeHoldAdjustmentDetails
fields.description: Details of any adjustment related to the holding or releasing of a payment.

fields.name: typeLocalOffersCashbackDetails
fields.description: Details of a cashback amount given by a Square Local Offers seller to their customer for a purchase.

fields.name: typeLocalOffersFeeDetails
fields.description:
Details of a commission fee paid by a Square Local Offers seller to Square for
a purchase discovered through Square Local Offers.

fields.name: typeOpenDisputeDetails
fields.description: Details of any open disputes.

fields.name: typeOtherAdjustmentDetails
fields.description: Details of any other type of adjustments that don't fall under existing types.

fields.name: typeOtherDetails
fields.description: Details of any other type that does not belong in the rest of the types.

fields.name: typePercentageProcessingRepaymentDetails
fields.description:
Details of withheld funds from a payment to cover a negative balance. It's an
installment to repay the amount from a dispute that had been offset during
Percentage Processing enrollment.

fields.name: typePercentageProcessingRepaymentReversedDetails
fields.description:
Details of the reversal of a percentage processing repayment that happens for
example when a refund is issued for a payment.

fields.name: typeProcessingFeeDetails
fields.description:
Details of the processing fee for a payment. If sellers opt for Gross
Settlement, i.e., direct bank withdrawal instead of deducting fees from daily
sales, the processing fee is recorded separately as a new payout entry, not
part of the CHARGE payout entry.

fields.name: typeProcessingFeeRefundDetails
fields.description:
Details of the processing fee for a payment refund issued by sellers enrolled
in Gross Settlement. The refunded processing fee is recorded separately as a
new payout entry, not part of the REFUND payout entry.

fields.name: typeRefundDetails
fields.description: Details of a refund for an existing card payment.

fields.name: typeReleaseAdjustmentDetails
fields.description: Details of fees released for adjustments.

fields.name: typeReserveHoldDetails
fields.description: Details of fees paid for funding risk reserve.

fields.name: typeReserveReleaseDetails
fields.description: Details of fees released from risk reserve.

fields.name: typeSquareCapitalPaymentDetails
fields.description: Details of capital merchant cash advance (MCA) assessments.

fields.name: typeSquareCapitalReversedPaymentDetails
fields.description: Details of capital merchant cash advance (MCA) assessment refunds.

fields.name: typeSquarePayrollTransferDetails
fields.description: Details of a payroll payment that was transferred to a team members bank account.

fields.name: typeSquarePayrollTransferReversedDetails
fields.description: Details of a payroll payment to a team members bank account that was deposited back to the sellers account by Square.

fields.name: typeTaxOnFeeDetails
fields.description: Details of tax paid on fee amounts.

fields.name: typeThirdPartyFeeDetails
fields.description: Details of fees collected by a third-party platform.

fields.name: typeThirdPartyFeeRefundDetails
fields.description: Details of refunded fees from a third-party platform.

fields.name: typeUndoGiftCardLoadFeeRefundDetails
fields.description: Details of a reversed refund for a fee charged during the sale or reload of a gift card.

fields.name: typeUndoProcessingFeeRefundDetails
fields.description: Details of a reversed processing fee for a payment refund in a Gross Settlement payment.

types.name: ScheduledShift
types.description:
Represents a specific time slot in a work schedule.This object is used to manage the
lifecycle of a scheduled shift from the draft to published state. A scheduled shift contains
the latest draft shift details and current published shift details.
Permissions: TIMECARDS_READ

fields.name: createdAt
fields.description:
The timestamp of when the scheduled shift was created, in RFC 3339 format presented as UTC.
  
Examples for January 25th, 2020 6:25:34pm Pacific Standard Time:
  
UTC:  2020-01-26T02:25:34Z
  
Pacific Standard Time with UTC offset:  2020-01-25T18:25:34-08:00

fields.name: draftShiftDetails
fields.description:
The latest draft shift details for the scheduled shift. Draft shift details are used to
stage and manage shifts before publishing. This field is always present.

fields.name: id
fields.description: **Read only** The Square-issued ID of the scheduled shift.

fields.name: merchantId
fields.description: The Square-issued ID of the merchant.

fields.name: publishedShiftDetails
fields.description:
The current published (public) shift details for the scheduled shift. This field is
present only if the shift was published.

fields.name: updatedAt
fields.description:
The timestamp of when the scheduled shift was last updated, in RFC 3339 format presented as UTC.
  
Examples for January 25th, 2020 6:25:34pm Pacific Standard Time:
  
UTC:  2020-01-26T02:25:34Z
  
Pacific Standard Time with UTC offset:  2020-01-25T18:25:34-08:00

fields.name: version
fields.description:
**Read only** The current version of the scheduled shift, which is incremented with each update.
This field is used for [optimistic concurrency](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/build-basics/common-api-patterns/optimistic-concurrency)
control to ensure that requests don't overwrite data from another request.

inputFields.description:
A query filter to search for buyer-accessible appointment segments with service-providing team members matching the specified list of team member IDs.  Supported query expressions are
- `ANY`: return the appointment segments with team members whose IDs match any member in this list.
- `NONE`: return the appointment segments with team members whose IDs are not in this list.

types.description:

for an employee.This might include a record of the start and end times for breaks
taken during the shift.

Deprecated at Square API version 2025-05-21. Replaced by Timecard.
See the [migration notes](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/labor-api/what-it-does#migration-notes).
Permissions: TIMECARDS_READ

fields.name: createdAt
fields.description:

UTC:  2020-01-26T02:25:34Z
  
Pacific Standard Time with UTC offset:  2020-01-25T18:25:34-08:00

fields.description: The tips declared by the team member for the shift.

fields.description:
RFC 3339; shifted to the timezone + offset. Precision up to the minute is
respected; seconds are truncated.

fields.description: The UUID for this object.

fields.description:
The ID of the location this shift occurred at. The location should be based on
where the employee clocked in.

fields.name: merchantId
fields.description: The Square-issued ID of the merchant.

fields.name: startAt
fields.description:
RFC 3339; shifted to the location timezone + offset. Precision up to the
minute is respected; seconds are truncated.

fields.description:

on the `location_id`. Format: the IANA timezone database identifier for the
location timezone.

fields.name: updatedAt
fields.description:
A read-only timestamp in RFC 3339 format; presented in UTC.
  
Examples for January 25th, 2020 6:25:34pm Pacific Standard Time:
  
UTC:  2020-01-26T02:25:34Z
  
Pacific Standard Time with UTC offset:  2020-01-25T18:25:34-08:00

fields.name: version
fields.description:
Used for resolving concurrency issues. The request fails if the version
provided does not match the server version at the time of the request. If not provided,
Square executes a blind write; potentially overwriting data from another
write.

fields.name: wage
fields.description:
Job and pay related information. If the wage is not set on create, it defaults to a wage
of zero. If the title is not set on create, it defaults to the name of the role the employee
is assigned to, if any.

[RetrieveSubscription](api-endpoint:Subscriptions-RetrieveSubscription) with the query parameter
of `include=actions` or from 
[SearchSubscriptions](api-endpoint:Subscriptions-SearchSubscriptions) with the input parameter 
of `include:["actions"]`.

fields.name: canceledDate
fields.description:
The `YYYY-MM-DD`-formatted date (for example, 2013-01-15) to cancel the subscription, 
when the subscription status changes to `CANCELED` and the subscription billing stops.
  
If this field is not set, the subscription ends according its subscription plan.
  
This field cannot be updated, other than being cleared.

fields.name: card
fields.description:
The ID of the [subscriber's](entity:Customer) card
used to charge for the subscription.

fields.name: chargedThroughDate
fields.description:
The `YYYY-MM-DD`-formatted date up to when the subscriber is invoiced for the
subscription.
  
After the invoice is sent for a given billing period,
this date will be the last day of the billing period.
For example,
suppose for the month of May a subscriber gets an invoice
(or charged the card) on May 1. For the monthly billing scenario,
this date is then set to May 31.

fields.name: createdAt
fields.description:
The timestamp when the subscription was created, in RFC 3339 format.
  
Examples for January 25th, 2020 6:25:34pm Pacific Standard Time:
  
UTC:  2020-01-26T02:25:34Z
  
Pacific Standard Time with UTC offset:  2020-01-25T18:25:34-08:00

fields.description:
A custom price which overrides the cost of a subscription plan variation with `STATIC` pricing.
This field does not affect itemized subscriptions with `RELATIVE` pricing. Instead, 
you should edit the Subscription's [order template](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/subscriptions-api/manage-subscriptions#phases-and-order-templates).

The tax amount applied when billing the subscription. The

separator and without a `'%'` sign. For example, a value of `7.5`

that total being the cost of the item and $0.09 (9 cents) being tax.

inputFields.name: anyOf
inputFields.description:
Matches records where any of the provided sub-filters evaluate to true.
This works just like an OR operator in SQL.

When `null` is passed, matches all documents.
When an empty list is passed, this part of the filter matches no documents.

inputFields.name: equalToAnyOf
inputFields.description:
Matches records where the field value is equal to any of the provided values.
This works just like an IN operator in SQL.

When `null` is passed, matches all documents. When an empty list is passed,
this part of the filter matches no documents. When `null` is passed in the
list, this part of the filter matches records where the field value is `null`.

inputFields.name: not
inputFields.description:
Matches records where the provided sub-filter evaluates to false.
This works just like a NOT operator in SQL.

When `null` or an empty object is passed, matches no documents.

types.name: WorkweekConfig
types.description:
Sets the day of the week and hour of the day that a business starts a
workweek.This is used to calculate overtime pay.
Permissions: TIMECARDS_SETTINGS_READ

fields.name: createdAt
fields.description:
A read-only timestamp in RFC 3339 format; presented in UTC.
  
Examples for January 25th, 2020 6:25:34pm Pacific Standard Time:
  
UTC:  2020-01-26T02:25:34Z
  
Pacific Standard Time with UTC offset:  2020-01-25T18:25:34-08:00

fields.name: id
fields.description: The UUID for this object.

fields.name: merchantId
fields.description: The Square-issued ID of the merchant.

fields.name: startOfDayLocalTime
fields.description:
The local time at which a business week starts. Represented as a
string in `HH:MM` format (`HH:MM:SS` is also accepted, but seconds are
truncated).

fields.name: startOfWeek
fields.description:
The day of the week on which a business week starts for
compensation purposes.

fields.name: updatedAt
fields.description:
A read-only timestamp in RFC 3339 format; presented in UTC.
  
Examples for January 25th, 2020 6:25:34pm Pacific Standard Time:
  
UTC:  2020-01-26T02:25:34Z
  
Pacific Standard Time with UTC offset:  2020-01-25T18:25:34-08:00

fields.name: version
fields.description:
Used for resolving concurrency issues. The request fails if the version
provided does not match the server version at the time of the request. If not provided,
Square executes a blind write; potentially overwriting data from another
write.
